Firefighters managed to contain the blaze on Friday which broke out on the 7th floor of the building. CAPE TOWN/JOHANNESBURG - Officials are investigating the exact cause of a fire which ripped through the top section of Gauteng premier David Makhura's offices in Johannesburg.Firefighters managed to contain the blaze on Friday which broke out on the 7th floor of the building. All staff were evacuated and no one was hurt. Makhura says they will now start assessing the cost of the damage. Now that this fire has been put down on the seventh floor, we will assess the damage done. At the same time in the Eastern Cape on Friday, staff at the premier s office also had to be evacuated after the building caught alightProvincial government spokesperson Sonwabo Mbananga says the cause of the blaze at the Eastern Cape administrative office is still unknown. A portion of the building has been gutted, but a substantial part of the building seems to be unaffected. The extent of the damage will form part of an investigation. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)